groups.description:
Better Naked is a weekly weight management class which offers a weekly food taster, themed discussion topic, group support, motivation and lots of laughs along the way to you reaching your personal target weight.



And most importantly, we educate members in how to maintain that weight and put an end to yoyo dieting which is so damaging to your health.



Better Naked will help you to keep track of your progress, avoid pitfalls and record your achievements.



We will support and motivate you and we will focus on all the things you've worked for and achieved, and share in your excitement and celebrate with you.



Weight loss, motivation and support, weekly taster, weekly discussion topic, lots of laughter.  Refreshingly different. You make the choices.



Monday, Wednesday and Thursday every week from 6:30pm to 7:30pm.

groups.name: Pest Control
groups.description:
__Domestic Charges (including VAT)__
rats - £66 (includes 2 revisits which must be no more than 28 days between each visit)
mice - £66 (includes 2 revisits which must be no more than 28 days between each visit)
bedbugs - £180 (includes 1 revisit within 28 days of initial treatment)
cockroaches - £108 (includes 1 revisit within 28 days of initial treatment)
wasps - £60 plus an additional £24 to remove the nest (includes 1 revisit within 28 days of initial treatment if required)
fleas - £114 (includes 1 revisit within 28 days of initial treatment)
ants - £60 (revisit within 28 days of the initial treatment - £24)
pest identification £36
other insects upon identification - £60 (revisit within 28 days of the initial treatment - £24)
squirrels - £192 (includes 3 visits within 10 days between each visit)
bird pests - by quotation only
Prices correct for the period 1 April 2018 to 31 March 2019.

50% discount is available on production of valid housing benefit, income support or low income related benefit or Leisure Key Band A Holders (there is no discount for a second wasp nest).

__Please note: If you book a treatment and our officer visits, but cannot carry out a treatment, you will still be charged. This is because you are paying for an officer to visit your property.__

groups.description:
Bringing the full cinema experience for a fraction of the cost.

Family friendly film showing every month throughout summer on the 2nd Saturday at St Luke’s Parish Centre. Doors open 5pm. The film starts at 5.30pm.

During winter, doors open 4pm. The film starts 4.30pm.

There are seasonal visits from __Father Christmas__ and the __Easter Bunny__.
